F\text{ - student is in the first class}
L\text{ - student is in the last class}
A\text{ - student got an A}
P(F) = \frac{21}{51}
P(L) = \frac{30}{51}
P(A) = \frac{4}{51}
P(A|F) = \frac{1}{21}
P(A|L) = \frac{3}{30}
\begin{align} P(F|A)&=\frac{P(A|F)P(F)}{P(A)}\\ &=\frac{\frac{1}{21}\frac{21}{51}}{\frac{4}{51}}\\ &=\frac{1}{4}\\ \end{align}
